OL,4,Cchildren buried in septic tank
OL,6,FIn 2014, local historian Caroline
OL,7,FCorless, who had been researching the
OL,8,Fhome, discovered that 796 babies and
OL,9,Fchildren who died at the institution
OL,10,Fhad been buried in a disused
OL,11,Fsubterranean septic tank on the
OL,12,Fgrounds.
OL,14,FThe findings sent shockwaves across
OL,15,Fthe Republic of Ireland and globally,
OL,16,Fbut it was not for another decade that
OL,17,Fplans for the site's excavation were
OL,18,Fannounced, despite years of
OL,19,Fcampaigning by survivors and their
OL,20,Ffamilies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
