OL,6,FThat apology was "accompanied by a
OL,7,FGovernment Action Plan for Survivors
OL,8,Fproviding for actions under eight
OL,9,Fthemes including redress, access to
OL,10,Frecords and memorialisation," a
OL,11,Fspokesperson for the Irish government
OL,12,Fsaid.
OL,14,FThe Bon Secours Sisters also offered a
OL,15,F"profound apology" after acknowledging
OL,16,Fthe order had "failed to protect the
OL,17,Finherent dignity" of women and
OL,18,Fchildren in the Tuam home.
